Do The addition of default methods removes many of the reasons to use abstract classes?


CONSTRUCTOR : 
Abstract classes allow defining constructor 
Interface do not allow defining constructor 

Can Instantiate Both 

To use both's method in a class       : Extend or Implement in class

To use boths's method inside a method2 : use it as annonymous inner class inside the method2 : Closures in Java

	
	
FIELDS : 

Abstract classes allow non-static and non-final fields
interfaces' fields are inherently public, static, and final


METHODS : 
Abstract classes allows methods to be public, private, or protected
Interface methods are inherently public.


